-- Fox Says Super Bowl Was Most-Watched Program in U.S. Television History
-- B y   S t e v e n   F r o m m
-- 2011-02-07T20:17:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-07/fox-says-super-bowl-was-most-watched-program-in-u-s-television-history.html
Super Bowl XLV became the most-
watched U.S. television program ever, and Fox became the first
network to exceed 100 million viewers with 100.9 million for a
night in prime time, according to fast-national ratings released
by  Nielsen Media Research . The information was disclosed in a
release by  News Corp .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steven Fromm at 
 sfromm@bloomberg.net  